    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER PSO140-61 - REASSEMBLE -
        MAINSHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="10">
        <title>MAINSHAFT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a light coat of oil on all thrust washer faces (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301461">Figure 61</hotlnk>). The externally splined washer is positioned against the
                gear bore snap ring and the internally splined washer against the snap ring on the mainshaft.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301461" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301461" filename="../figg13/g1301461.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 61. Apply Oil on All Thrust Washer Faces</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 1st-reverse clutch collar between the mainshaft snap rings (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301462">Figure 62</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301462" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301462" filename="../figg13/g1301462.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 62. Install 1st-Reverse Clutch Collar</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 1st speed gear, complete with thrust washers, on the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301463">Figure 63</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301463" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301463" filename="../figg13/g1301463.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 63. Install 1st Speed Gear on Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 2nd speed gear on the mainshaft and secure with a mainshaft snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301464">Figure 64</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301464" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301464" filename="../figg13/g1301464.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 64. Install 2nd Speed Gear on Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the 2nd-3rd clutch collar onto the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301465">Figure 65</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301465" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301465" filename="../figg13/g1301465.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 65. Slide 2nd-3rd Clutch Collar onto Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 3rd speed gear on the mainshaft with the clutch teeth down (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301466">Figure 66</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301466" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301466" filename="../figg13/g1301466.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 66. Install 3rd Speed Gear on Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 4th speed gear and secure with a mainshaft snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301467">Figure 67</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301467" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301467" filename="../figg13/g1301467.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 67. Install 4th Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the 4th gear clutch collar onto the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301468">Figure 68</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301468" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301468" filename="../figg13/g1301468.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 68. Slide 4th Gear Clutch Collar onto Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 5th speed gear on the mainshaft and secure with a snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301469">Figure 69</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301469" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301469" filename="../figg13/g1301469.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 69. Install 5th Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the reverse gear and butt it against the 1st speed gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301470">Figure 70</hotlnk>). Secure with lockwire.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301470" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301470" filename="../figg13/g1301470.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 70. Install Reverse Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
